 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-subsequences-that-satisfy-the-given-sum-condition/&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are given an array of integers  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt;  and an integer  &lt;code&gt;target&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;the number of non-empty subsequences of  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt;  such that the sum of the minimum and maximum element on it is less or equal to  &lt;code&gt;target&lt;/code&gt; &lt;/em&gt;. Since the answer may be too large, return it &lt;strong&gt;modulo&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;code&gt;10^9 + 7&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [3,5,6,7], target = 9&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 4&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; There are 4 subsequences that satisfy the condition.&lt;br /&gt;
[3] -&amp;gt; Min value + max value &amp;lt;= target (3 + 3 &amp;lt;= 9)&lt;br /&gt;
[3,5] -&amp;gt; (3 + 5 &amp;lt;= 9)&lt;br /&gt;
[3,5,6] -&amp;gt; (3 + 6 &amp;lt;= 9)&lt;br /&gt;
[3,6] -&amp;gt; (3 + 6 &amp;lt;= 9)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [3,3,6,8], target = 10&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 6&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; There are 6 subsequences that satisfy the condition. (nums can have repeated numbers).&lt;br /&gt;
[3] , [3] , [3,3], [3,6] , [3,6] , [3,3,6]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-3&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-3&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 3:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [2,3,3,4,6,7], target = 12&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 61&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; There are 63 non-empty subsequences, two of them do not satisfy the condition ([6,7], [7]).&lt;br /&gt;
Number of valid subsequences (63 - 2 = 61).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;解題思路&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#解題思路&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 解題思路&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;solution&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#solution&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
